{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 01:43:29.406863", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 3-tier Clos using EBGP (super-spine AS65000 → spines → leaves). Each leaf advertises its directly connected /24; all interconnects are /31 in 172.16.0.0/16.\\n- Focused end hosts: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 on leaf_router_0_0) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 on leaf_router_0_1).\\n\\nKey Symptoms Observed\\n- Reachability tests show widespread success across the fabric, except anomalies when pc_0_0 is the source:\\n  - get_reachability: tests sourced from pc_0_0 report status “unknown” (no pings sent/returned), while pc_0_1 to multiple destinations is OK with low RTTs.\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2): “ping: connect: Network is unreachable”.\\n  - pc_0_0 → 10.0.0.1 (its default-gateway in-subnet): initially “Network is unreachable”; when forced with -I eth0, intermittent responses with packet loss (2/3 received).\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1) → 10.0.0.2: intermittent connectivity (2/3 received, then subsequent 10-ping attempt timed out).\\n\\nControl-Plane and Fabric Health\\n- BGP RIBs:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 has connected 10.0.0.0/24 via its host-facing interface and BGP-learned 10.x.y.0/24 routes via 172.16.1.0 (uplink to spine). Multiple /31s are directly connected. This is consistent and stable.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, and super_spine_router_0 all show full tables for all 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24s via expected next-hops, with ECMP to superspine where appropriate. No signs of missing routes or BGP instability.\\n- Conclusion: EBGP control plane across the Clos fabric is healthy.\\n\\nAccess/Edge Findings (pc_0_0 side)\\n- pc_0_0 interface and routing:\\n  - ip route: only 10.0.0.0/24 connected; there is no default route. pc_0_1 has default via 10.0.1.1, indicating pc_0_0 deviates from expected host config.\\n  - ip link/ethtool: eth0 shows link problems; ethtool reports “Link detected: no”; ip -s link shows state DOWN; counters minimal with some RX drops. ARP neighbor for 10.0.0.1 is stuck in DELAY (unresolved/unstable).\\n- Leaf-facing interface toward pc_0_0:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 eth8 (10.0.0.1/24) is UP/LOWER_UP; counters are very low; ARP table empty; intermittent ICMP replies from 10.0.0.2 with loss.\\n\\nAccess/Edge Findings (pc_0_1 side)\\n- pc_0_1 has default route via 10.0.1.1, pings to its gateway 10.0.1.1 are clean, and it can reach 10.0.0.1 across the fabric with 0% loss and low RTT. No issues observed on this host or its leaf.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n1) Physical/link-layer instability on pc_0_0’s access interface (eth0):\\n   - Evidence: ethtool “Link detected: no”; ip -s link state DOWN; ARP not stable; intermittent ICMP success with loss from/to the leaf.\\n   - Impact: Unreliable L2 connectivity between pc_0_0 and leaf_router_0_0.\\n\\n2) Missing default route on pc_0_0:\\n   - Evidence: pc_0_0 routing table lacks a default route; “Network is unreachable” for off-subnet destinations; pc_0_1 has the expected default route.\\n   - Impact: Even if the link were up, pc_0_0 would be unable to reach off-subnet destinations without policy/explicit routes.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Fault is localized to the access link between pc_0_0 (eth0) and leaf_router_0_0’s host-facing interface (eth8).\\n- The core/spine/superspine EBGP fabric is operating normally; anomalies are confined to the pc_0_0 access segment and pc_0_0 host configuration.\\n\\nMost Probable Root Cause\\n- Primary: Layer-1/Layer-2 link failure or flapping at pc_0_0’s NIC (eth0) resulting in no carrier and unstable ARP/ICMP.\\n- Secondary: Host routing misconfiguration on pc_0_0 (no default route), which would prevent off-subnet reachability even if the link were stable.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Host 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) is effectively isolated/unreliable due to link issues and lacks off-subnet routing. All other tested hosts and the EBGP fabric appear healthy., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='41b45f94-1629-460f-a30e-006839789378'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
